I have a component which receive a prop named _params_ which is a shape with the attribute **name**.

I use this prop in an TextField element,, but it stills give me the **no-unused-prop-types** error.

Please refer to the code below

``` javascript
const ClientFilters = ({ fetch, fetching, params, onFilterNameChange }) => (
  <form style={styles.container} onSubmit={() => fetch()}>
    <TextField
      hintText="Pesquisa por nome"
      floatingLabelText="Nome"
      floatingLabelFixed
      value={params.name}
      onChange={onFilterNameChange}
    />
    <RaisedButton
      secondary
      icon={<FontIcon className="material-icons">search</FontIcon>}
      style={styles.searchButton}
      type="submit"
      disabled={fetching}
    />
  </form>
)

ClientFilters.propTypes = {
  fetch: PropTypes.func.isRequired,
  fetching: PropTypes.bool.isRequired,
  params: PropTypes.shape({
    name: PropTypes.string.isRequired,
  }),
  onFilterNameChange: PropTypes.func.isRequired,
}

export default ClientFilters
```

Any ideas on that? Is it a bug or am I doing anything wrong?
Thanks

